{{Chembox <!-- Images --> | ImageFile = 9-Crown-3.svg | ImageSize = 120px | ImageAlt = <!-- Names --> | IUPACName = 1,4,7-Trioxonane | OtherNames = 1,4,7-Trioxacyclononane; Ethylene oxide trimer <!-- Sections --> | Section1 = {{Chembox Identifiers | CASNo = 27725-91-3 | PubChem = 552016 | ChEBI = 32400 | Beilstein = 1421638 | ChemSpiderID = 480221 | SMILES = C1COCCOCCO1 | InChI=1S/C6H12O3/c1-2-8-5-6-9-4-3-7-1/h1-6H2 | InChIKey=RCIDBLLMZGGECJ-UHFFFAOYSA-N }} | Section2 = {{Chembox Properties | C=6|H=12|O=3 | Appearance = | Density = | MeltingPt = | BoilingPt = | Solubility = }} | Section3 = {{Chembox Hazards | MainHazards = | FlashPt = | AutoignitionPt = }} }}
'''9-Crown-3''', also called '''1,4,7-trioxonane''' or '''1,4,7-trioxacyclononane''' is a [[crown ether]] with the formula C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>12</sub>O<sub>3</sub>. It is a cyclic [[Trimer (chemistry)|trimer]] of [[ethylene oxide]] which is specific for the lithium cation. Its [[point group]] is S<sub>3</sub>.
==See also== *[[1,4-Dioxane]]
