Bacterial ''thiol disulfide oxidoreductases (TDOR)'' are bacterial enzymes which, along with unfolded proteins, are [[Secretory pathway|pumped out]] of a bacterial cell that allow for adhesion and [[biofilm]] development, and generally disease development.<ref>http://phys.org/news/2015-10-reveal-approach-combating-bacterial-diseases.html</ref>
